TextBody:
Hey Phi,

We believe the issue with the FS_BrokenInheritance job have been resolved. For our next steps, we'd like to upgrade to the latest version of Netwrix Enterprise Auditor/StealthAUDIT and remove any pre-existing tables and views with the FS_BrokenInheritance prefix. The job does this anyways, but a clean slate never hurts.

Please use the link below to schedule a remote session for us to upgrade:

https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=bp8ptQGW11GaE9kFsTC0K1cXXgrZsrHUW6kjDLYH.jA-Z&MeetingID=qh115Zgjf.Zta9ZrRtlWejiIsv2AHUAVOsLCqIe2Zzs-Z

Before the upgrade meeting, please complete the following:


	Take a backup/snapshot of the StealthAUDIT console server
	Take a backup/snapshot of the StealthAUDIT database
	Download the latest installers from the Netwrix Portal


Let me know if you have any questions!

Thank you,
Tay Caliguiri

Senior Technical Support Engineer
__________________ _________
Cybersecurity That Works for You

300 Spectrum Ctr Dr #200, Irvine, CA 92618
www.netwrix.com

Ticket Number: 00422123
Ticket Subject: Error Running Broken Inheritance Job "Invalid object name 'SA_FS_BrokenInheritance_Details'. Could not use view or function 'SA_FS_BrokenInheritance_UniqueTrustees' because of binding errors."
Ticket Details: I saw this was reported in case 00382569. The solution in this case was to replace the job with an older version. I confirmed this did work, but the version shipping out of the box is having this error in some environments.

ERROR DataAnalysis:SQLScripting ExecuteNonQuery "Invalid object name 'SA_FS_BrokenInheritance_Details'. Could not use view or function 'SA_FS_BrokenInheritance_UniqueTrustees' because of binding errors."

I could not reproduce this in my lab. Investigating the issue at the customers it appeared the #tmpPaths and the permissionsCompaison table both had data.

Thank you!

Tay Caliguiri
Senior Technical Support Engineer
